# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets needed by install/generate-iso.sh and the iDRAC automation.
# These files live under  secrets/  which is GITIGNORED — never commit them.
# This .example file is the only tracked artifact; it documents what to create.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Create the secrets/ directory at the repo root and populate:
#
#   secrets/pull-secret.json   Red Hat pull secret. Get it from:
#                              https://console.redhat.com/openshift/install/pull-secret
#                              (Downloads → Tokens → "Pull secret"). Raw JSON.
#
#   secrets/ssh-key.pub        SSH PUBLIC key for node access/debug, e.g.:
#                              ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -f secrets/ssh-key -N ''
#                              (keep the private key secrets/ssh-key out of git too)
#
# Optional — only if you script iDRAC actions (boot/virtual-media). Source this
# file (cp to secrets/credentials.env first) before running iDRAC helpers:
#
#   IDRAC_USER=root
#   IDRAC_PASS='<the iDRAC root password — ROTATE the one shared in chat>'
#   IDRAC_NODE1=192.168.101.5
#   IDRAC_NODE2=192.168.101.6
#   IDRAC_NODE3=192.168.101.7
#
# The cluster's own kubeconfig + kubeadmin password are generated by the
# installer into install/_artifacts/auth/ (also gitignored).
